  "prompt": "Are there legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several legal frameworks designed to combat money laundering, including:\n\n1. International Frameworks:\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n\n2. National Legislations:\n- Bank Secrecy Act (USA)\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) regulations\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) requirements\n- Suspicious Activity Reporting (SAR) protocols\n\n3. Key Prevention Strategies:\n- Customer due diligence\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Reporting suspicious transactions\n- Financial institution compliance programs\n\n4. Enforcement Mechanisms:\n- Criminal prosecutions\n- Asset seizure\n- Significant financial penalties\n- International cooperation between law enforcement agencies\n\n5. Specific Sectors Covered:\n- Banking\n- Real estate\n- Cryptocurrency exchanges\n- Gambling industries\n- Financial services\n\nThese frameworks aim to detect, prevent, and prosecute money laundering activities by establishing comprehensive regulatory standards and reporting mechanisms across different jurisdictions.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any specific aspect of money laundering legal frameworks?",
